caption: The food is so flavourful. I ordered the jerk chicken and it was cooked to perfection. The rum punch had a strong kick to it as well - can’t complain! The service was fantastic as well. I loved it here.
The food was fine. The place needs a makeover and better team.

We decided to stop in here and were surprised. The place was empty but we sat and ordered some food and drinks. Everything was delicious.  We are so happy to support this establishment  and will support again.

Unfortunately, we ate our meal before I could get a good picture of it . We came to Lila Cafe and ordered a sorrel drink, rum punch, oxtail empanadas, and the grilled jerk chicken. Everything was delicious. It wasn't busy but even so the waitress was super nice and attentive. She made me a bomb rum punch. They were out of oxtails but I will definitely try it next time I come. The jerk chicken was spicy and jerky, which I love! The veggie medley was also very delicious as well as the rice. The sauce with the empanadas is bomb too! Will definitely return!

The calamari is really nice and my boyfriend loved the curry shrimp! We shared a chocolate cake and it was so good! We love coming here for food because the price is just right and the staff is always nice.
Great restaurant. High recommend these guys.
Angel was a great server! Beer and margarita specials were amazing. Definitely will recommend to anyone visiting Brooklyn NY on a budget.
Thanks a bunch lila cafe! I would definitely come again, and I would recommend this to everyone.
Always a great high quality meal. Friendly outgoing staff and energetic yet cozy atmosphere.
Excellent staff, welcoming and comfortable atmosphere....superb entrees! Highly recommended!
Great local restaurant. High quality food and hometown atmosphere.
Friendly, great staff. The family loved the meals and my petite filet was amazingly tender and cooked perfectly.
Very laid back atmosphere. The food is good, cocktails are great and the staff is friendly.
Delicious food and excellent service. We have never been disappointed here.
Came here for a friend's baby shower. The food was really delicious, and the mimosa was quite yummy!
Paula is the best! She has great personality and recommended drinks that fit. We had a blast! Taken care of like kings!
I went to Lila Cafe for the first time. And food was great, drinks were great. Server was very nice and flexible. I totally recommend. Outdoor sitting is available and they are COVID safe!

I go with my wife to this great restaurant  a lot! This is the best place to grab a bite.  I visit this spot routinely. The meals are great, the workers are friendly and the payment is good. I enjoy being in this place to have a good lunch.

I had a wonderful time there, my 1st time there, I had the garden salad & Codfish fritters, Stephanie Bates was there singing some great old School soul music that I really enjoyed. I will tell my friends & family about this place.
Went to Lila this past Sunday with a few friends.  Service was great and so was the food. The setting is very cozy as well.

Had brunch with my family today at Lila’s Cafe. Loved the cozy ambience; the food was authentically Caribbean, tasty and beautifully presented; and the service was outstanding. Doesn’t look like much from the outside but you won’t be disappointed once you enter. Well look forward to visiting again!!
Had an amazing brunch with attentive service! Their weekend brunch special is a free mimosa with your meal! Definitely Coming back soon.
Delicious whiting and cassava fries! Amazing service and can’t wait to come back for their events.
Love the brunch here! We had the whiting and the chef’s special coconut French toast which was fantastic and reasonable! The staff is super friendly, we will be back fo sho

10/1/2019 The atmosphere was okay The food is pricey, I was hoping it was worth it.. I waited about 20 min after I ordered SMH the food was horrible The food taste like it was reheated in the microwave (I can tell the difference)because it was served Luke warm & everything on my plate was dried out....I was so hungry I started eating After the 2nd bite I was completely turned off.. It’s not worth eating here I won’t recommend  Then I saw the cook who comes out the kitchen, sits at one of the tables where some people are and had a whole conversation for about 30 min having a good ol time A chef never leaves the kitchen. But then again all the cook had to do was heat the food up in the microwave if a order comes in  At that point I asked for the bill, left and won’t be returning
Beautiful decor.  Attentive service and delicious food. What more do you want from a restaurant?

I came here for brunch with my best girl friend and everyone was welcoming and kind. We were seated and provided menus and told about drink specials. We ordered two apps and two brunch menu items and everything was delicious. 3 rum punches later, which are not the best (taste like a tequila sunrise with too much artificial lemon juice) I have a buzz but needed an extra shot to get it, and the manager comped the shots "YAY!". Over all 4 stars but the hospitality is FIVE STAR QUALITY.
Nice ambiance, service, food quality.
Phenomenal food and such incredible staff! The staff make you feel so comfortable and welcomed. Have the cod fritters!!
The best place to be for a relaxed weekday or turnt up weekend night. Great dinner date environment or chilled. 🧡🧡
Barbara was friendly and so was waitress but the cook was slow..Food took to long..Will give it another try another day Will submit a 2nd review..
I've been here multiple times and everytime I loved it. The workers are really nice people. The food was very good and so was the drinks.
Good service and good food too

Kymaada the staff was very professional and gave me great ideas on what to eat I selected the oxtail , peas n rice and for dessert the raisin rum cheese cake It was all delicious !!! Didn’t t leave anything on my plate This will be my usual spot for when I want to taste real Jamaican food!! Will call my dad to tell him found a place that cooks as good as he does ! 👍🏽👍🏽👍🏽👍🏽👍🏽
Perfectly seasoned chicken, delicious waffles, and lovely wait staff. Come here!

Nice intimate setting with R&B playing at a moderate level. At the firm suggestion of the very professional, attentive, and gracious hostess Shanay, I dined in and ordered ox tails, along with rice and peas and sweet plantains. Delicious! With some room left for dessert, I ordered chocolate cake and ice cream. Only having warm cake with the cold ice cream would improve the experience. And the price is VERY reasonable.  9 out of 10 experience. And I will return

I live in the neighborhood and decided to try the place . The food is AH-mazingggg ! Brunch weekends are an absolute delight and you get a free mimosa with any entree!!!!! Dinner is lit af, im usually a steak person but them oxtails, rice and peas and Mac is to die for 😭
Amazing food, amazing service , great prices ! Couldn’t get any better .
Awesome place. Great food. Amazing drinks.
Great place to eat and hang out with friends. Love the food and love the drinks.
I absolutely love the oxtails. The customer service is also very good.

Went on open mike night was pleasantly surprised. The atmosphere was very nice...staff was super friendly drinks were 👍.....have visited here before and had the Salmon.....excellent......had the escovitch(?) Fish.....not so good but it's worth working my way through the menu to find all the good stuff.
Thursday night karaoke
The food, service, ambiance.... Everything was on point! Such a warm and friendly restaurant but with some great Friday night dinner vibes. Will be back again!
Great food, and amazing service!
Great
I have never in my life been to a restaurant where everything was great. I’m honestly amazed. The plates were absolutely beautiful as well.  I’ll be back to try brunch.

The service here is great. The drinks are really good too. I will say that the dinner service tastes much better than the brunch did on Sunday but the brunch prices are great. I had brunch here  on Easter so it was a different menu than what I had this past Sunday and I’m guessing they had a different cook too. I will definitely be back for dinner. Brunch maybe not so much.
Service and food were excellent!!

I’m writing a very late review but had to remember to leave a review nonetheless. I’ve been to this establishment for brunch now 3 times and the very last time was the best experience I’ve ever had. My friend and I went to Lila Cafe for brunch on Easter and the food was AMAZING!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! I’ve been to this establishment twice before for Sunday brunch and have always been less than impressed but love their drinks and the staff is friendly so I continue to go.  While my friend and I originally were going to order something safe like shrimp and fries, I noticed that they had an Easter menu. I ordered the coconut French Toast and my friend ordered the blueberry waffles. EVERYTHING WAS AMAZING. My friends Chicken was cooked PERFECTLY! My French Toast was PERFECT! My grits were PERFECT! My eggs were PERFECT! The seasoning on everything was great. I seriously hope that they continue to make brunch the way they did on Easter. Whoever made the food we had obviously loves what they do and simply gets it.  Please please please please please please keep up the great work and don’t let whoever made that Easter brunch leave. I know it sounds ridiculous but it honestly was great and I’ve been thinking about that French Toast all week!
It was great.  The food, the people, the acoustics and the music absolutely fantastic.  I truly enjoyed.

I love this spot. I have the pleasure of living around the corner from them so I am there frequently. Its nice inside and they even have a cute little backyard. Everything that I have tried there has been good with the exception of the mixed vegetables.  My favorite thing to eat there are the cod fish fritters and I just love the staff there, they are always warm to me and my family/friends. I  always recommend them to everyone .

Lila is a lovely place to eat drink and enjoy some live music. The rum wings are wonderful and tasty and well seasoned. The coconut shrimp and plantains are magnificent. Plantains lightly fried and sweet, tasted exceptional. The rum punch was flavorful and tasty. The bartender and staff were pleasant, friendly and helpful. Nothing but good food, good vibes, and cheerful environment. Must go back to enjoy more of the menu.

1st time here and it won't be the last!!  Food is great. We were getting ready to leave and then the Dj came in. Sundays from 2-7...Ordered another rum punch and chilled a little longer. For a spur of the moment place it worked out perfectly. The place isn't too big, so if you can make reservations. Other than that...Enjoy!!!

The grilled Salmon was the best I've ever had. It melted in my mouth. The cassava fries were fried just right. Honestly everyone I was with loved their food tremendously. If you want good eating and delicious Island food, this is the spot. I'll differently be back for their salmon.

I went here this evening with my husband & 2 brothers to see LA Blacksmith & his band. The music was awesome. He played Jazz & old school music. The food was great also. Our waitress Kim was amazing...The manager Barbara is so nice. I surely will be going back. I found a new spot for the grown folks...
crab cakes had no crab. cute small place. more for intimate crowds.
Lila’s cafe is the #1 place to dine It’s a “jewel” hidden in Bedstuy!!! The food is DELICIOUS 😋 LOVE THIS PLACE 🥰😘🥰

The atmosphere was great enjoy the open mic people excellent the food needs work the grilled jerk chicken was over cooked the plantains were burn the rice had no taste going to get it another shot because it's a business in my community and I like supporting the black own business where I live.

Lila’ Cafe is one of my favorite restaurant to go to. Food is excellent, ambiance is amazing and customer service is top notch. Manager always comes out to greet. My food arrived very quickly plus when my friends or family members ordered we are so deep in our conversations and just having a good time we didn’t even realized the food was coming out. I always bring someone when to go to get a taste of the food and enjoy the experience with me. Music and the painting on the wall is just amazing all around. If you haven’t tried Lila’s Cafe please do so you won’t regret it. I travel 45 mins for this food and I will keep going back every chance I get. Five stars across the board.
Everything was delicious and the service was even better

The live music is always good. Tonight it was a Blues show with Beareather Reddy vocalist and Lafayette Harris, Jr. on piano. Every show I have seen has been great. Only a two drink minimum, no  entry fee. Next show is on March 13th with  Kim Clarke jazz bassist. Staff are very nice, I love the art work and the atmosphere.
Love the food here.
Very nice atmosphere, delicious food and drinks. The band was superb. Only opinion is that if they would advertise much more extensively more people would be there for the entertainment.
Everytime i have visited this establishment it has been a pleasure...the food is fantastic and Miss Barbara has a great ORA
Great food and accommodating staff!
It was great. The food, the decor n the waitress was wonderful.  I will definitely return.
Great food and atmosphere.

First Lila Cafe is a real cozy an comfortable place, I assume it recently opened so it's great to have new businesses in the Stuy. The space is a little tight but for wheelchairs I think they may be able to manuver I'm the Cafe. The service is friendly, Monica our server was great. The drinks were Strong but reasonably priced. We went for Brunch, it's a very small but Caribbean themed menu. Everything that we ordered was amazing. The Ackee an Saltfish amazing, the cornmeal porridge amazing, the Steak an eggs mouthwatering goodness. The wait is a little long but it's cool cause you can chat it up with whoever an just relax. There is also a DJ that started up on the tail end of our meal. Also certain foods were a little over salted but still a great meal. I would DEFINETLY put this on my lists of favorite spots.
The food was absolutely delicious. I will definitely come back

Me and my bf went for breakfast.  The owner is very nice the food was amazing the price was great. Food was well seasoned cheese grits shrimp and fish was wonderful. Nice portion for a good price.  Owner was attentive staff was friendly.  I will be going back.
I came here twice and both times the service and food was amazing
Its a very nice place to go to eat.

Food was good but it took forever to come out. My party were continually served the wrong plates. The waitress was nice and professional but they had nothing I wanted. No fish. No grits. No empanada. All things that are clearly on the menu. I hope they prepare themselves better and maybe hire more people. The music was very loud. The crowd was kinda 40+ so that was kinda surprising. It is a nice place overall and I hope they improve their service.
Excellent for and drinks cozy spot
Very good orange juice! 👍

I have ate at this place before, a few times when it first opened.  But lately the service has gotten really bad.  I waited almost an hour for a simple order.  When I said something, they told me that the cook did not read my order by mistake... I waited some more for my order then I was told that there was only one cook cooking.  I tried to sit, give them my best waiting as possible.  I ordered my son a small chocolate ice cream, that also took a million years to get to me.  I mean, Calm on!  With all that waiting, and to win the customer back, I would had at least offered the child the ice cream for free.  But we got nothing!  I don't think I will visit this place again.  Do I recommend?  I once did, but not anymore.

The customer service sucks. It took me 26 minutes to get my food and 15 minutes to get my bill.This resturant is specifically for young people. The Loud music and uncontrolled bar area made my visit horrible. The food was cold and expensive. I'd never eat here again.
Wonderful place with great food ( I recommend the Bake Mac & Cheese) Quick and great service! Will totally be back. 100% recommend.

This place is amazing. The food was great and the service was awesome. The drinks were mixed so well and tasted so good I couldn't have just one. I ordered multiple food and drinks and now I'm hoping they will cater an event for me. My only suggestion is that they market and promote because this is one of Brooklyn's best kept secret!
Couldn't give 0 stars so here we go. The "rasta pasta" was watery and bland. The oxtails were scary. The curry sucked, there is no Caribbean flare here. Very disappointing.

I stop in here while at the laundromat in my neighborhood. I had to say I was pleasantly surprised. The server Mary was very attentive and salad and salmon I had was scrumptious. In total a salad and salmon was $24 not bad by my standards. My part of bedstuy is a food dessert in terms of sit down spots. So to see Lila cafe is very welcoming for my neighborhood. This will be a spot I frequent a lot. I think it’s black owned as well which gives me more an incentive to patronize the place.

Been here for the opening weekend one day for dinner and one day for their mother's day brunch. Friendly athmosphere, great food. The servers still finding their way, the first time they forgot to ask me what sides I wanted and the second time the server had a lil issue with the timing of the courses. In time I am sure they will get their rhythm. They are very nice.  This place gives me a reason to come to Brooklyn and visit my family more often. 😁
